  <prompt>
    Create the GET /api/v1/field-mappings/profiles/{sourceEntity}/{targetEntity} endpoint in the
    BFF API. This endpoint returns a single profile with all its rules for a specific entity pair.
    Used by PCF controls to get mappings when a record is selected.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer with expertise in .NET 8 Minimal API development. Follow ADR-001
    for API patterns, ADR-008 for endpoint filters, ADR-019 for ProblemDetails error responses.
  </role>

  <goal>
    GET /api/v1/field-mappings/profiles/{sourceEntity}/{targetEntity} endpoint implemented that
    returns a profile with all its rules. Returns 404 if no profile exists for the entity pair.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      PCF controls need to quickly look up if a mapping exists for a given entity pair. This
      endpoint provides that lookup with full rule details so the control can apply mappings
      without additional API calls.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/FieldMappings/FieldMappingEndpoints.cs - From task 013</file>
      <file>projects/events-and-workflow-automation-r1/spec.md - API Requirements section</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">Must use Minimal API pattern</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">Return ProblemDetails 404 if not found</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">Include all rules in response (eager load)</constraint>
  </constraints>

